    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1217"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1217">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7108.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Admiral <persName type="from">Winslow</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of the Navy</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Flagship “San Diego</hi>,” <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Topolobampo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 21, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>M–3240. Indians again raiding Yaqui Valley, attacking settlers at Ontagota and
                    the experimental station at San Pedro. Reported that troops and people were
                    deserting Ontagota and that General Obregon has ordered six hundred cavalry from
                    Esperanza who should arrive at Ontagota between 8 and 12 tonight. One thousand
                    troops have left Magdalena enroute to Yaqui Valley via Guaymas and it is hoped
                    that they will arrive in the valley tomorrow. I do not understand that Americans
                    are leaving the valley. Am I to land troops if General is willing? Immediate
                    answer requested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winslow</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
